  "title" : "Apache PDFBox - merge documents without loading objects to memory",
  "body" : "<p>I'm trying to merge PDF documents using <a href=\"https://pdfbox.apache.org/docs/2.0.1/javadocs/org/apache/pdfbox/multipdf/PDFMergerUtility.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">PDFMergerUtility</a>. I was thinking about mergeDocuments() method but when I looked into the source code, the files are loaded as in-memory <a href=\"https://javadoc.io/static/org.apache.pdfbox/pdfbox/3.0.6/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/PDDocument.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">PDDocuments</a>, which I'm trying to avoid, because my application works with huge images that are exported to pdf and creating PDDocument containing these images causes <code>OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space</code>.</p>\n<p>Is there any way to merge these documents without loading the whole objects to memory, using PDFBox?</p>\n"
}